<paragraph blockId="1.[151,428,1525,1586]" box="[151,280,1560,1586]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,270,1560,1586]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Figs. 1–8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1629,2028]" box="[151,432,1629,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1629,1655]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Length</emphasis>
: male 7.00 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1629,2028]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,215]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,486,1666,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">External morphology.</emphasis>
General color black with white to yellowish bullae on dorsum, particularly numerous on pronotum and veins of forewings (
<figureCitation box="[716,785,1704,1730]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Prothoracic legs raptorial-like, femur and tibia broad, flattened, foliaceous (
<figureCitation box="[418,495,1741,1767]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Head small, much narrower than pronotum as in all known species; crown narrower than width of eyes at base, produced distally beyond anterior margin of eyes about ¼ of its entire median length, anterior margin angulate, submargin deeply rugulose; ocelli prominent, near anterior margin next to eyes; eyes large, bulbous laterally, occupying about 2/3 of entire dorsal area of head; pronotum very large, about twice median length of head as in all species, surface marked with numerous bullae (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1420,1890,1916]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig 2</figureCitation>
); mesonotum very large, median length greater than median length of pronotum; forewings; forewings long, expanded subapically, veins lined with bullae, three anteapical cells present, outer one closed; appendix well developed; clypeus distinctly elevated with nearly complete, prominent, median longitudinal carina; clypellus with lateral margins divergent apically, with complete median longitudinal carina, separated from the clypeus carina by the transclypeal suture.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" startId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" targetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1918,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,322,1918,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">FIGURES 1–8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Nielson, 2010" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2010" box="[329,487,1918,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gabrita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erwini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[329,487,1918,1941]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Gabrita erwini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[500,586,1918,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[500,579,1918,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,775]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,378,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer in lateral view long and narrow, without processes (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1195,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); pregenital plate in ventral view very long and narrow, glabrous except for few apical setae (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1073,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig 5</figureCitation>
); style in lateral view elongate with prominent, angulate process medially on inner lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[968,1042,226,252]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); aedeagus in lateral and ventral views very long, about one-half times as long as style, tubular, narrow, needlelike at apical 4/5, sharply pointed distally, about as long as plate, gonopore cryptic (
<figureCitation box="[827,938,301,327]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[167,1427,260,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[157,1442,250,1913]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Gabrita erwini, sp. nov. Fig. 1. Dorsal habitus; Fig. 2. Foreleg, lateral view; Fig. 3. Head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; Fig. 4. Male pygofer, lateral view; Fig. 5. Subgenital plate, ventral view; Fig. 6. Right style, lateral view; Fig. 7. Aedeagus, lateral view; Fig. 8. Aedeagus, ventral view. (All views 50X except dorsal habitus, 7.50X.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5304685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5304685/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,775]" box="[197,419,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,412,338,364]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Female unknown</emphasis>
